column1: 146003;instagram;2018-12-05 15:34:23;FALSE;"to the girls who have loved someone who didn't deserve them
column2: i salute you for your very act of loving. for having the power to love the people who can't love you the way you deserve to be loved. i salute you because even when it hurts like hell

column1: i salute you for your belief that people can change. that maybe one day
column2: he would realise just how important you are. that one morning
column3: he will see all your efforts and appreciate it. that a time will come and he will take into consideration all the emotions you invested in him. that one special moment
column4: he would simply decide to reciprocate the love you deserve.

column1: i salute you for giving so much more than what you're receiving.
i salute you because you've been used and yet you choose to forgive. you've been hurt yet you choose yo heal. you've been taken for granted yet you choose to exert effort beyond comprehension.
i salute you because no matter how wounded your soul is
column2: no matter how damaged your heart is
column3: you always choose to love. you always choose to learn
column4: forget and move forward. you still choose to accept the pain

column1: i salute you because after all
column2: loving is never easy. loving can be scary. loving can be tortuous. loving can be distasteful. but you still choose to see love for all its fascinating attributes. you still choose to love
column3: and not just love the easy people
column4: or the people who can give you the world. you didn't love the right people
column5: you loved all the wrong ones and that reflects nothing but total bravery.

146027;instagram;2018-12-05 16:06:06;TRUE;;we as women are choosing to advocate for the #metoomovement via instagram because we want to speak out on a large platform where our posts can be recognized by not only our followers but other women through the explore page
column2: reposts and other female celebrities. skeptics might state that women can be making up these stories and falsely accusing male counterparts to gain recognition and publicity. some may also argue that these women have waited too long to speak out about their experiences with sexual harassment or abuse. nonetheless
column3: our strong and powerful sisters stand united against harsh commentary and will fight for our movement through educating the public through a multitude of female survivor stories. furthermore
column5: we hope to establish safe spaces in which women can feel comfortable to speak of their prior experienced and ways they can bring about change in society. we want to educate women on coping mechanisms as well as ways they can protect themselves in future incidents. we want to reform prior societal standards of female treatment. our goal behind this movement is to give females a voice in a society that has been dominated by males for far too long. we not only want to shed the light on celebrities but also underprivileged women who face harassment on a daily basis. this movement will give females freedom over their own bodies and justice to receive the fair  treatment that have  failed to receive. #nomeansno #women #metoo #womensrights #respect #love #strength #passion #woman;en;#MeTooMovement

column2: arunny* shared her devastating story of sexual harassment with us. a year on and with care's help
column3: things are changing in arunny's workplace – for the better! read on to hear from arunny 👇 ""in the past
column4: i faced harassment from my boss. he used to overuse his power and take advantage of me. whenever he saw me alone
column5: he would find opportunities to harass me
column6: coming up behind and hugging me. ""he never did it to anyone else
column7: only me because i didn’t report his behaviour to anyone. i didn’t know who to report to and if i mentioned this
column8: people did not pay attention since they thought it was only a joke. ""now it has changed. ""i feel safe at work because no one is messing with me now.” care has been working with factories like arunny’s to help management ensure women feel safe from sexual harassment.

column1: we want to support workplaces to develop positive policies
column2: increase women’s confidence to stand up to and report sexual harassment
column3: and encourage improved laws and regulations across the mekong region.

column1: arunny sees this is working. ""this behaviour has stopped because my factory has training on those topics. everyone in my factory has learnt about sexual harassment
column2: so they all understand that it’s not ok. ""my factory also has policies to prevent sexual harassment and management announce these to everyone. when i heard the announcement of sexual harassment policies in my factory
column3: i was so joyful and very supportive of this because they also included verbal sexual harassment as well as physical sexual harassment in these policies. ""we also have a sexual harassment committee
column4: so that people can feel comfort in reporting. ""the harassers now don’t dare to act like in the past. no one dares to harass women anymore. ""now i feel safe when i’m at work.” .

column1: فمینیسم اومد تا به داد زن‌هایی برسه که ظالمانه امکان پیشرفت ازشون گرفته شده بود، ولی الان تبدیل شده به چیزی که من واژه‌ای بهتر از واژنیسم براش سراغ ندارم، و می‌گه اگه کسی آلت جنسی زنونه لای پاهاش باشه، حتماً حق با اونه. شاهد این ادعا هم کسانی هستند که توی همین یکی دو سال اخیر همه‌ی زندگیشون رفته رو هوا، اون هم فقط به خاطر تهمت یکی دو تا زن و بدون این که چیزی توی دادگاه اثبات بشه. اما مهم‌تر از زندگی یکی دو تا سلبریتی آثار اجتماعی این طرز تفکره. بلومبرگ اخیراً یه مقاله منتشر کرده که می‌گه بعد از گل کردن اون هشتگِ metoo دیگه توی بعضی اداره‌ها کارمندان زن رو تو پارتی‌ها راه نمی‌دن، و اگه این راه ندادن امکان‌پذیر نباشه، حتی پارتی‌ها رو کنسل می‌کنند، یا سعی می‌کنند باهاشون بیرون نرن، یا کم پیش میاد تو اتاقی که پنجره‌های بزرگ نداره و درش باز نیست، باهاشون جلسه بذارند.‌ و ازین قبیل موارد. بلومبرگ نوشته فمینیست‌ها معتقدند این اتفاقات امکان پیشرفت زنان رو ازشون خواهد گرفت. انصافاً هم درست فکر می‌کنند. پس چی شد؟ فمینیسمی که اومده بود جلوی ظلم به زنان رو بگیره، خودش داره آب می‌ریزه تو آسیاب ظلم به زن‌ها. اما چرا همچین شده؟ به نظر من فقط به یه دلیل، و اون اینه که فمینیسم بای‌دیفالت مردها رو دشمن زن‌ها فرض می‌کنه، و این طرز تفکر باعث شده هر اختلاف و تقابلِ موردی تعمیم پیدا کنه به جنگ بین کل مردها و کل زن‌ها. بدیهیه در یه چنین شرایطی، اولش مردها سعی می‌کنند خودشون رو از زن‌ها جدا کنند تا شمشیر نخورند، و بدتر، اگه این روی‌کرد ادامه داشته باشه و مردها باور کنند واقعاً با زن‌ها دشمنند، یقیناً به برخوردهای عملی‌تر و خشن‌تری دست خواهند زد. مثلاً ممکنه یه روزی دوباره برگردیم به روش‌هایی مثل زنده‌به‌گور کردن دختران!
پ.ن: برای دسترسی به لینک مقاله‌ی بلومبرگ مراجعه کنید به لینک بیو و مطلب «واژنیسم».

column1: to the girls who have loved someone who didn't deserve them
column2: i salute you for your very act of loving. for having the power to love the people who can't love you the way you deserve to be loved. i salute you because even when it hurts like hell

column1: i salute you for your belief that people can change. that maybe one day
column2: he would realise just how important you are. that one morning
column3: he will see all your efforts and appreciate it. that a time will come and he will take into consideration all the emotions you invested in him. that one special moment
column4: he would simply decide to reciprocate the love you deserve.

column1: i salute you for giving so much more than what you're receiving.
i salute you because you've been used and yet you choose to forgive. you've been hurt yet you choose yo heal. you've been taken for granted yet you choose to exert effort beyond comprehension.
i salute you because no matter how wounded your soul is
column2: no matter how damaged your heart is
column3: you always choose to love. you always choose to learn
column4: forget and move forward. you still choose to accept the pain

column1: i salute you because after all
column2: loving is never easy. loving can be scary. loving can be tortuous. loving can be distasteful. but you still choose to see love for all its fascinating attributes. you still choose to love
column3: and not just love the easy people
column4: or the people who can give you the world. you didn't love the right people
column5: you loved all the wrong ones and that reflects nothing but total bravery.

column1: 146099;instagram;2018-12-05 17:55:11;FALSE;“i looked away from the road just long enough to notice that he was no longer wearing his seatbelt. i wasn’t sure when he had unbuckled it or why

this is a man’s world – so sang james brown – and most notably
column2: the working world is a man’s world.

column1: despite the government target for boards and executive committees of the uk’s top businesses to comprise 33% women by 2020
column2: recent reviews and investigations appear to suggest the professional world is regressing.

column1: the hampton-alexander ftse women leaders review published earlier this month (november 2018) highlighted a sliding scale for female leaders. the number of female ceos in the ftse 350 now stands at 12 – a decrease on 15 in 2017 and 18 in 2016.

column3: been some progress; “the number of women on ftse 100 boards has exceeded 30% for the first time”. but this success is short-lived as the report continues to demonstrate that leadership remains firmly male-dominated; five ftse 350 companies maintain all male boards
column4: while 75 have just one female board member.

column1: 146119;instagram;2018-12-05 18:05:43;FALSE;"i’d be lying if i said that i’ve encountered the same obstacles as someone who identifies as transgender
column2: even though the lgbtq acronym joins us as one community

column1: despite the increase in visibility of transgender people
column2: many still risk disproportionately higher rates of discrimination
column3: social stigma and systemic inequality than any other community - especially for transgender people of color
as an openly gay entrepreneur know there is no better time than now to be more actively involved in my community and support conversation around topics

column2: i set many goals at the forefront -  sustainable manufacturing practices
column3: eco-friendly alternatives to design and packaging & formulating products with truly natural & safe ingredients

column1: i have realized that our mission can be stronger than this. so
column2: i’m ready to shift and broaden my responsibilities by establishing ourselves as more than just another consumer brand - stimulating intelligent discourse & bringing new meaning to a corporations social responsibility

column1: we all have a story. and right now
column2: our transgender brothers and sisters need a safe platform. see
column3: through the stories that shed tears
column5: i am learning how to shape history & pursue a brighter tomorrow in every capacity. more importantly
column6: i am being reminded just how much we are in this together

column2: we may have been called something other than our name
column3: pushed into a corner and even excluded. but damn
column4: we know the power of our voice. we know the power of peacefully seeking change. we know the power of facing fear. we know the power of living a life as we choose

column2: i am launching a limited edition handcrafted bath bomb
column3: in the colors of the trans flag - i’m calling it trans is beeautiful
column4: in tribute to the words of @lavernecox. with every purchase
column5: we will donate 100% of profits to the @translifeline
column6: a trans-led 501(c)(3) non-profit organization dedicated to improving the quality of trans lives.

column1: 146121;instagram;2018-12-05 18:07:14;FALSE;i was tagged in this video and i wanted to give my thoughts on it. let’s start with the definition of what groping actually is. it means to touch someone for sexual pleasure usually against their will. so based on that definition i don’t think most of these touches fit that definition. a woman in a club can get touched by someone trying to get her attention
column2: by someone trying to get past her
column3: or even be touched by other women. so i think it’s very misleading to equate a woman getting touched 40 times in an hour as a statistic for sexual harassment! it’s not like everybody is just rubbing the woman’s ass or touching her pussy. i think stuff like this just shows how hard people are willing to go to make it seem like everything is some kind of violation of a woman. we all know that there is some inappropriate touching or groping that happens in nightclubs.  but whether it’s appropriate or not is based largely on how the woman feels about the person doing it. most women don’t claim to be harassed when someone they’re attracted to touches them when they’re in the club. and in order to be harassed someone has to make it known that they have a problem with a particular behavior and the person continues to do it. so i think this whole experiment is rooted in victimology (not a real word) and an attempt to make it seem like women are constantly being harassed and taken advantage of by sexual predators when they’re out in a club. tag someone that would like my page or the things i talk about! ↗️ turn on your post notifications!! tag someone that would like my page or the things i talk about!  #terryderon #victim #metoo #harrassment #dating #relationships #message #nolie #wordstoliveby #truestory #trust #respect #realtalk #imjustsaying #facts #truelove #accurate #reallytho #truthbetold #loyalty #straightup #factsonly #worstfeeling #lonely #trustissues #breakups;;en;#terryderon

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

column1: the most anticipated event of 2019 doesn’t have to be personal. maybe you’re already looming forward to a concert that you have tickets for. maybe you’re looking forward to a new tv show that you know is starting in the new year. or maybe it’s something as simple as knowing you still be trying something new.
as we collectively gear up for another turn around the sun
column2: bent but not breaking would like to hear what you’re hoping and dreaming that 2019 will bring. the format is up to you:
a paragraph or even a poem about your top 2019 hopes and dreams.

column1: or paraphrase a meaningful song or story. images can say so much; send a photograph or video that conveys what is most likely to put a smile on your face in the coming year.
if you’re one of those who truly embraces the concept of an uncertain future
column2: maybe there’s no specific event or thing that gets you excited about the year to come. if it’s more of a feeling
column3: or a prediction or general trend
column4: that’s fine too. as long as you can put it into words (or photos or a video)
column5: then we encourage you to share it. message us on our facebook or instagram
column6: or post it on your own instagram and facebook accounts. you can post on your own accounts with the hashtag #bentbutnotbreaking2019 (just make sure your settings are public so we can see the post)

column1: we will be sending out some gifts to the post we love the most and we’ll also be publishing some of your hopes and dreams for 2019 in future content
column2: so keep checking for your feature .

column1: knowing how to read the signs and trusting your instincts is what it's all about. why does this keep happening to me you say to yourself. what you should be asking is how can i be better at reading the signs and identify danger and be a better observer.

in the next week i will be launching my blog ""safe space"" for those who want to tell their stories about abuse and their experience with toxic people. i will also post information about dangerous personality types and how to read them from top experts and have joined forces with a womans abuse hotline as well as healthyplace
column2: and will have links available for those seeking further help.

column1: an investment in knowledge could not only save your relationship
column3: state of mind and finances but also your life.

column1: sources tell tmz that the disgraced studio mogul harvey weinstein fired off several emails tuesday to his people in the media he once worked with
column2: back when he was a hollywood mogul.

column1: he did not send one to tmz
column2: but we've obtained a copy from a source. the reason for the emails is pretty clear -- weinstein feels his side of the nyc rape case isn't getting enough attention.

column1: 146312;instagram;2018-12-05 22:28:38;FALSE;"let me preface this post by saying i have a ton of respect for the women behind the #metoo movement. the work they’ve done over the last year
column3: has wrenched loose some long-overdue justice for women who had been assaulted and silenced by powerful men and by the good old boys’ club that enabled them. 🔽

column2: i co-edited a #book of #essays by dozens of sexual assault survivors—most of them women
column3: some of them men. not one of the authors i worked with belittled or ignored the plight of men who had been sexually abused. ⬇️

column1: along with the fantastic editorial staff at philadelphia weekly
column2: i tried my hardest to make sure the project was inclusive and respectful of the needs of all communities who are plagued by sexual assault. ⬇️

column1: in the last two years or so
column2: i’ve seen a dramatic shift in the public conversation about sexual assault. it is rife with infighting
column3: and it is openly contemptuous toward men
column4: even if they’ve been sexually assaulted
column5: because they are presumed to be pawns of the patriarchy. ⬇️

column1: there are millions of men in the united states recovering from sexual abuse. many of them have long-lasting mental health problems and find it difficult to ask for help because of how they’ve been socialized. ⬇️
i can’t speak for all of them
column2: but i ask that you take this post to heart and think about how the framing of this issue may affect male sexual abuse survivors

column1: 146319;instagram;2018-12-05 22:41:43;FALSE;"what is it about people who knock down a womyn after finding out she’s experienced sexual trauma and then decides to embrace her sexuality in her own way ... what is so threatening to them? what is it???
it’s her body and her choice to move forward in whatever way feels right to her ... period *
in my book the storyteller’s throne
column2: the main character experiences childhood sexual abuse and it plays out in ways that are sexual
column4: investigative and pure to her experience ... *

column1: i wrote it without judgement on her ... i wrote it as a testament to the ways that womyn heal ... i wrote it as an unapologetic look at what female sexuality can be ... i wrote it knowing it would piss people off ... but it just is. *

those of us who have experienced sexual trauma heal in many ways and that healing takes many forms ... and it’s up to us ... as a people ... to let go of the judgements ... to take on the hard work of allowing people their journey ... to find true empathy ... that’s the only way we heal as a bigger community ... *
so i ask you ... what judgements can you let go of today? *

column2: tarana burke is a powerful blessing! this quote is taken from her recent interview with @nationmag. the full interview is available online & is linked in my bio @thejoyexpert. ms. burke speaks about how parents can support their children after sexual assault. she shares what she learned from parenting her daughter. when asked
column3: “how do we talk to our children about sexual violence
column4: but also help them understand they can find pleasure and joy in their bodies!” ms. burke concludes
column5: “this was a hard one and i struggled with it all through my daughter’s preteen years... i think nonsexual pleasure is one of the main entry points to talk about it
column6: too: nonsexual pleasure in your body. we talk about joy a lot in our family
column7: because it’s central to my work...teaching your child to curate joy in their life very early.”";en;#Repost

column1: 146358;instagram;2018-12-05 23:29:33;FALSE;"we’ve talked about the consequences that follow relationships in the office
column2: but we haven’t discussed any real world examples of office romances turning sour (until now!). an article written by jenna mcgregor for the washington post
column3: “intel’s ceo resigned after violating a no-dating rule. more companies are adding them in the #metoo era
column4: ” highlights what could potentially happen to a superior who is romantically involved with a lower-level employee. the article tells how intel’s ceo
column6: had stepped down because he violated the companies “non-fraternization” policy that has been in place since 2011 because of his “past consensual relationship” with another intel employee. mcgregor explains how more and more companies are now strictly abiding by these laws in the wake of the #metoo era. they are terrified that an incident will be brought up and their company will be under ethical fire for allowing coworker relations to occur.

column1: it’s extremely common for companies to have non-fraternization rules to avoid messy breakups and other distractions from a professional work environment
column2: but that doesn’t mean there won’t be couples who go behind their superiors backs. *sidenote: by no means does this mean that every employee that’s had a romantic relationship with another coworker should be subject to backlash from the #metoo community
column3: but it sure has people watching their backs when put into this situation.* mcgregor also makes a point to address offices becoming a more comfortable environment for employees to enjoy themselves
column4: and that’s not a bad thing! the problem arises when people are not able to distinguish what is work and what is play. she explains that new tech startups are becoming places where employees can have a great time
column5: but it can easily turn into “confusing things you do at bars with things you do at work.” the free-flowing environment of these companies can cause employees to blur the lines between what is and what isn’t acceptable in the office
column6: especially when everyone feels comfortable with each other. upper management and other coworkers use friendlier language
column8: and drink together after a long day.";;en;#MeToo

column1: i tell a piece of my story in my book

column5: but we forget that children think differently than we do.

column1: 146390;instagram;2018-12-06 00:56:16;FALSE;"excited & grateful to be back leading nia
column4: one of my favorite @debbierosas classic nia routines.

column2: nia helped me learn to love my body. (which was a broken
column3: unsafe place.) recovering from rape & navigating sobriety
column4: i saw an ad for a free week of classes at the synergy studio. i took my first real live yoga class. sweet peace. afterward i heard curious sigh sounds from the other studio. what is going on in there? sweaty women rolling around on the floor moaning pleasurably. wild! could i do that??? after my first class with @journeyoflife i was hooked. i felt silly
column5: but i felt alive! finding physical joy

how do you find and use your voice?  please share in the comments .

column1: 1) tuck your chin and shrug your shoulders. this will alleviate some of the pressure and make it hard for them to continue to squeeze.
2) be aware. look too see what leg they have forward
column2: isolate that same side arm.(one hand under and gripping over their wrist with your second hand as extra support)

column1: 3) get better leverage by flaring your elbow open that's under the arm your not isolating.
4)slide out of the way toward the side they don't have their foot forward and circle around to face them.
this technique emphasizes the concept of not trying to muscle our way out of something
column2: but instead figure out how to use your own body weight and leverage to escape.

column1: you can not learn if you think you already know everything.

do not judge anyone. you could be sitting in their same seat a week from now. life is unpredictable and today you have only experienced one perspective of it out of the 7.6 billion entirely different perspectives on this earth right now.
our time here is limited. every second you waste brings you another empty second to the end.
your life is art. you won't find another like it anywhere you go.
life seems dark and cruel sometimes
column2: i know. but you can be the spark that brings back the light in this world. love at every opportunity you have.

column1: i am lucky enough to own this painting now. sneha sent it to me weeks ago because it meant so much to my heart and i have been tryinf to find the most perfect frame so i can hang it in my bedroom. i haven't found that frame yet
column2: i feel it will speak to me and feel right once i walk into the right vintage shop. but until then

column5: and it reminds me of myself
column6: the pain i sometimes harbor and that emotional release into something neverending...like the ocean.

column1: 146512;instagram;2018-12-06 04:31:16;FALSE;"“what good do your words do if they can’t understand you? don’t go talking that shit....” | the mother edition @erykahbadu⁣
i took a spiritual journey through her art and it genuinely redefined my heart. i learned the feeling of love from multiple perspectives and felt the frequency of love in the highest degrees. ⁣

i found that love was intelligence. something that needed to be studied before it was felt. a certain responsibility comes with feeling something so deeply. one that can only be understood with emotional maturity. ⁣

love can’t be defined by feelings; it can only be measured through them. the definition of love can only be expressed through connection. two important components: compatibility and adaptability. how deeply can you understand your partner? how well can you respond to your partner’s evolution? love is when your emotions learn to speak the same language. when hearts learn to have healthy communication with one another. ⁣

column1: 146538;instagram;2018-12-06 05:25:34;FALSE;"truth post 2: abuse is not a joke. my last truth post talked about my mother. it talked about the abuse i watched her receive from the corner of the room when i was a four year old girl. that fucks with your head. it makes you think that it is okay for someone to grab you that way and to throw you and do whatever they want to you.

my first boyfriend was abusive in more ways than one. he cheated on me with five girls. people ask why i didn’t leave him. the truth? i was scared. scared for my life and scared for his. i lost thirty pounds in two months partly because of the emotional abuse i went through dating him and never feeling good enough because i was cheated on regularly. people i didn’t even know would detail them catching him in the act. i tried to leave him when i saw messages between him and another girl. “i want to bend you over and…” you can finish the rest. it hurt. i told him we were done. i almost died because of it. he pushed his foot down on the gas pedal and hit 70… 80… 90… i grabbed the steering wheel. i begged him to stop and told him that i would stay with him. two weeks later i was on my porch with his arm around my neck choking me while he accused me of cheating on him. ironic.

column2: i had a boyfriend that would scream in my face to the point he was spitting on me while i would sit there fighting tears. i left him.

column1: i dated another guy. things were good for a while
column2: about six months i’d say. but then one night
column3: things changed. he almost kissed a girl in front of me. next thing i know he’s telling me that i am not good enough for him and i know that i’m not good enough and i should give up and let him have sex with me after i said no. he grabbed my wrists hard enough to leave red marks. his hand had at one point moved to my throat. tears formed in my eyes. he said “whatever” and rolled over. i went to the living room
column5: and cried myself to sleep. i kept it between him and i. i suffered alone through a period of not feeling good enough because some dumb boy told me that i wasn’t and my previous experiences made me believe that.

column1: so before getting into it i highly recommend reading jenn pelly’s feature article on pitchfork (https://pitchfork.com/features/article/reckoning-with-pinegrove/). it’s a really involving and clever piece of investigative journalism that tells the story of evan hall after being accused of sexual coercion. the mess that it was is neatly explained by pelly
column2: involving multiple perspectives and insights. it’s overall message suggests that there is real individuals to grow and learn from their mistakes in the age of #metoo. defs read it because i think its important.

column3: mostly written and recorded a year ago let delayed due to the circumstances outlined above. the record has this strange familiarity that goes beyond this though
column4: the melodies and choruses feel so familiar yet stray from being annoyingly so through just how comforting their soft-indie country sound. i absolutely adore the licking twang of peters’ voice
column5: it elevates his statements and centrepieces to evoke vulnerability and yearning. this album contains story of relationships
column6: lovely odes to friends and a strong emphasis on internal balance. it’s eery but the focus on themes of self-improvement and taking responsibility is both a pertinent message for peters’ but it extends beyond the band itself and becomes a message of import in general. it’s the kinda album that gently edges into your melancholy and reminds you “whatever you’re feeling is natural”. #pinegrove#skylight#indierock#indiemusic#indiepop#country#countrymusic#alternativecountry#alternativemusic#midwestemo#emo#emomusic#midwestmusic#alternativerock#experimentalrock#languageartsrock#rootsrock#montclair#tawnypeaks#gifts#halfwaif#jeffrosenstock#hollowandakimbo#goodgoodblood#musicreview#albumreview#anaustralian";;en;#metoo.

146547;instagram;2018-12-06 05:31:45;FALSE;ಕರ್ನಾಟಕ ಬಿಜೆಪಿಯಲ್ಲಿ  #metoo! “ನಾನು ಚೆನ್ನಾಗಿದ್ದೀನಿ ಎಲ್ಲರೂ ಕರೀತಾರೆ…” ಎಂದ ಪಾಲಿಕೆ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಸದಸ್ಯೆ! ನಾನು ಚೆನ್ನಾಗಿದ್ದೀನಿ ಎಲ್ಲರೂ ಕರೀತಾರೆ… ಹೋಗಲಿಲ್ಲ ಅಂದರೆ ಅಧಿಕಾರ ತಪ್ಪಿಸ್ತಾರೆ… ಇಂತಹದ್ದೊಂದು ಗಂಭೀರ ಆರೋಪ ಮಾಡಿರುವುದು ಅಟ್ಟೂರು ವಾರ್ಡ್‍ನ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಸದಸ್ಯೆ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಅವರು. 12 ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿಗಳ ಸದಸ್ಯರ ಆಯ್ಕೆಗೆ ಇಂದು ಬೆಳಗ್ಗೆ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಕಚೇರಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ಮಾಜಿ ಡಿಸಿಎಂ ಆರ್.ಅಶೋಕ್, ಶಾಸಕರಾದ ಎಸ್.ಆರ್.ವಿಶ್ವನಾಥ್, ಸತೀಶ್‍ರೆಡ್ಡಿ, ಉದಯ್ ಗರುಡಾಚಾರ್, ಪ್ರತಿಪಕ್ಷದ ನಾಯಕ ಪದ್ಮನಾಭರೆಡ್ಡಿ ನೇತೃತ್ವದಲ್ಲಿ ಚರ್ಚೆ ನಡೆಯಿತು. ಯಲಹಂಕ ವಿಧಾನಸಭಾ ಕ್ಷೇತ್ರದ ವಾರ್ಡ್ ನಂ.3ರ ಅಟ್ಟೂರು ವಾರ್ಡ್ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಸದಸ್ಯೆ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಅವರು ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿ ಸದಸ್ಯತ್ವಕ್ಕೆ ಆಕಾಂಕ್ಷಿ ಆಗಿದ್ದರು. ಎಲ್ಲ ಸಮಿತಿಗೂ ಬಿಜೆಪಿಯವರಿಗೆ ಐದು ಸದಸ್ಯ ಸ್ಥಾನ ಸಿಕ್ಕಿದೆ. 60 ಜನರಿಗೆ ಅವಕಾಶ ಸಿಕ್ಕಿದೆ. ಉಳಿದ 40 ಮಂದಿಗೆ ಸಿಗಲಿಲ್ಲ. ಹಾಗಾಗಿ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿಗೂ ಸದಸ್ಯತ್ವ ಕೈ ತಪ್ಪಿದೆ. ಇದರಿಂದ ವಿಚಲಿತರಾದ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಪಾಲಿಕೆ ಆವರಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಅಳುತ್ತಾ ಇದ್ದರು. ಈ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲಿ ಮಾಧ್ಯಮದವರು ಏಕೆ ಅಳುತ್ತಿದ್ದೀರಾ ಎಂದು ಪ್ರಶ್ನಿಸಿದಾಗ, ನಾನು ಚೆನ್ನಾಗಿದ್ದೀನಿ, ಕೆಲವರು ಕರೆದಾಗ ಹೋಗಲ್ಲ. ಹಾಗಾಗಿ ನನಗೆ ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿ ಸದಸ್ಯ ಸ್ಥಾನ ಕೈ ತಪ್ಪಿಸಿದ್ದಾರೆ ಎಂದು ಅಳುತ್ತಾ ಹೇಳಿದರೆಂದು ವರದಿಗಳು ಪ್ರಕಟವಾಗಿದೆ. #jokersofbjpkarnataka #saynoforbjp #bjpmetoo;;en;#MeToo!, #jokersofbjpkarnataka, #saynoforbjp, ಮಾಡಿರುವುದು ಅಟ್ಟೂರು ವಾರ್ಡ್‍ನ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಸದಸ್ಯೆ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಅವರು . 12 ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿಗಳ ಸದಸ್ಯರ ಆಯ್ಕೆಗೆ ಇಂದು ಬೆಳಗ್ಗೆ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಕಚೇರಿಯಲ್ಲಿ ಮಾಜಿ ಡಿಸಿಎಂ ಆರ್.ಅಶೋಕ್ , ಶಾಸಕರಾದ ಎಸ್.ಆರ್.ವಿಶ್ವನಾಥ್ , ಸತೀಶ್‍ರೆಡ್ಡಿ , ಉದಯ್ ಗರುಡಾಚಾರ್ , ಪ್ರತಿಪಕ್ಷದ ನಾಯಕ ಪದ್ಮನಾಭರೆಡ್ಡಿ ನೇತೃತ್ವದಲ್ಲಿ ಚರ್ಚೆ ನಡೆಯಿತು . ಯಲಹಂಕ ವಿಧಾನಸಭಾ ಕ್ಷೇತ್ರದ ವಾರ್ಡ್ ನಂ.3ರ ಅಟ್ಟೂರು ವಾರ್ಡ್ ಬಿಜೆಪಿ ಸದಸ್ಯೆ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಅವರು ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿ ಸದಸ್ಯತ್ವಕ್ಕೆ ಆಕಾಂಕ್ಷಿ ಆಗಿದ್ದರು . ಎಲ್ಲ ಸಮಿತಿಗೂ ಬಿಜೆಪಿಯವರಿಗೆ ಐದು ಸದಸ್ಯ ಸ್ಥಾನ ಸಿಕ್ಕಿದೆ . 60 ಜನರಿಗೆ ಅವಕಾಶ ಸಿಕ್ಕಿದೆ . ಉಳಿದ 40 ಮಂದಿಗೆ ಸಿಗಲಿಲ್ಲ . ಹಾಗಾಗಿ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿಗೂ ಸದಸ್ಯತ್ವ ಕೈ ತಪ್ಪಿದೆ . ಇದರಿಂದ ವಿಚಲಿತರಾದ ನೇತ್ರಾ ಪಲ್ಲವಿ ಪಾಲಿಕೆ ಆವರಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಅಳುತ್ತಾ ಇದ್ದರು . ಈ ಸಂದರ್ಭದಲ್ಲಿ ಮಾಧ್ಯಮದವರು ಏಕೆ ಅಳುತ್ತಿದ್ದೀರಾ ಎಂದು ಪ್ರಶ್ನಿಸಿದಾಗ , ನಾನು ಚೆನ್ನಾಗಿದ್ದೀನಿ , ಕೆಲವರು ಕರೆದಾಗ ಹೋಗಲ್ಲ . ಹಾಗಾಗಿ ನನಗೆ ಸ್ಥಾಯಿ ಸಮಿತಿ ಸದಸ್ಯ ಸ್ಥಾನ ಕೈ ತಪ್ಪಿಸಿದ್ದಾರೆ ಎಂದು ಅಳುತ್ತಾ ಹೇಳಿದರೆಂದು ವರದಿಗಳು ಪ್ರಕಟವಾಗಿದೆ .

column1: power is a fragile commodity. it can be taken in a moment
column2: yet takes years to rebuild. to lose your power is to lose part of your identity. i know the pain of losing my power in a moment of helplessness. fear gripping my body
column3: being out of control of what happened next. i am joined in my pain by an entire community of incredibly strong human beings who have been through the darkest valleys and have made it to the other side. these pieces are real words from sexual assault survivors who have had their power taken from them in an unspeakable moment. from then on
column4: we have been fighting to survive
column5: to rebuild the shell of who we used to be. part of regaining your power is finding your voice again. i believe these words symbolize the exact moment their authors realized their power was never gone in the first place
column6: just buried under layers of trauma. jessica found her voice as she addressed a courtroom with the backing of 160 other survivors. emily found her voice in a letter she wrote to her abuser. i found my voice when i stopped trying to hide. i decided to dedicate my senior thesis to the words of survivors because these words are our survival

146574;instagram;2018-12-06 06:29:08;FALSE;"today has been one of the tougher days for me.  i grew up learning how to stuff down my emotions and finding external ways to let them out.  finally i had experiences this year that i had no choice but to face these beautiful demons as they come head on.  in one moment my entire life changed drastically and any feeling of security went out the window and it’s been an on and off struggle since. i don’t share this to just to share it
column2: it’s because going through this doesn’t mean shit if i keep it to myself.  if i can be a voice or remind even one other human that they are not alone when they feel pain
column3: i feel mine has a purpose.  ptsd is no joke and so much of my life has been not believing that my feelings were valid because i would compare someone else’s life to mine and tell myself to suck it up.  for the first time in my life i’m allowing myself to be truly vulnerable.  all day i’ve felt a need to protect myself for absolutely no apparent reason.  it’s been excruciatingly overwhelming.  then someone reached out to me and told me that the word mental illness can be changed if we change the “i” to “we”.... ‘i’llness becomes ‘we’llness.  then this song came on my playlist reminding me that these still are the good old days
column5: if we allow ourselves the help we need and feel worthy of the life we deserve.  life is always going to change and it will never be perfect until we find beauty in the things that seem miserable and seemingly out of place.  i truly appreciate everyone who had had a part in my journey. .

column1: 146629;instagram;2018-12-06 08:53:35;FALSE;"บิล คลินตัน กับการ ""โกหก"" ที่ทำให้เขาถูกถอดถอนจากตำแหน่งประธานาธิบดี .

กระแส #metoo ในปัจจุบัน ทำให้ผู้ชายที่มีอำนาจเป็นผู้บริหารในองค์กรต่างๆ ต้องออกจากตำแหน่ง หรือสูญเสียสถานภาพเดิมไปกันหลายคน กับข้อกล่าวหาประพฤติไม่เหมาะสมทางเพศ ตั้งแต่การใช้สถานะที่เหนือกว่าฉวยโอกาสลวนลามไปจนถึงการข่มขืนลูกจ้างหรือผู้อยู่ใต้บังคับบัญชา .
ความเคลื่อนไหวทางสังคมในครั้งนี้ทำให้หลายคนหวนนึกถึงกรณีอื้อฉาวในปี 1998 ซึ่งทำให้ บิล คลินตัน ประธานาธิบดีสหรัฐฯ จากพรรคเดโมแครตในขณะนั้นต้องเผชิญกับกระบวนการถอดถอนจากตำแหน่ง

โมนิกา ลูวินสกี อดีตเด็กฝึกงานทำเนียบขาวซึ่งมีสัมพันธ์ทางเพศกับคลินตันเคยพูดถึงความสัมพันธ์ครั้งนั้นว่ามันเป็นความสัมพันธ์ที่มาจากความยินยอมทั้งสองฝ่าย แต่หลังเกิดกระแส #metoo เธอให้ความเห็นผ่าน vanity fair ว่าตอนนี้เธอก็ไม่แน่ใจแล้วว่าสิ่งที่เกิดขึ้นเป็นความยินยอมหรือความจำยอมกันแน่

เขาเป็นเจ้านายของฉัน เขาคือคนที่มีอำนาจมากที่สุดในโลก เขาอายุมากกว่าฉัน 27 ปี กับประสบการณ์ชีวิตที่รู้อะไรมากกว่าฉัน ตอนนั้นเขาอยู่ในจุดสูงสุดของชีวิตการงาน ส่วนฉันเพิ่งจะได้ทำงานแรกหลังจบมหาวิทยาลัย""

อย่างไรก็ดี ตอนนั้นการแสวงประโยชน์ทางเพศของผู้มีอำนาจไม่ได้ถูกเพ่งเล็งมากเหมือนตอนนี้ (ซึ่งรุนแรงถึงขนาดทำให้ผู้ชายหลายคนต้องพ้นจากตำแหน่งโดยไม่ต้องขึ้นไปโต้แย้งถึงชั้นศาล) ความสัมพันธ์ของทั้งคู่แม้จะอื้อฉาวแต่ก็ไม่ได้เป็นหัวใจหลักที่ทำให้คลินตันถูกดำเนินการถอดถอน แต่เป็นเพราะการเบิกความเท็จ และการขัดขวางกระบวนการยุติธรรม
อ่านต่อเต็ม ๆ ได้ที่เพจ the people และเว็บไซต์ thepeople.co

กระแส  ในปัจจุบัน ทำให้ผู้ชายที่มีอำนาจเป็นผู้บริหารในองค์กรต่างๆ ต้องออกจากตำแหน่ง หรือสูญเสียสถานภาพเดิมไปกันหลายคน กับข้อกล่าวหาประพฤติไม่เหมาะสมทางเพศ ตั้งแต่การใช้สถานะที่เหนือกว่าฉวยโอกาสลวนลามไปจนถึงการข่มขืนลูกจ้างหรือผู้อยู่ใต้บังคับบัญชา .
ความเคลื่อนไหวทางสังคมในครั้งนี้ทำให้หลายคนหวนนึกถึงกรณีอื้อฉาวในปี 1998 ซึ่งทำให้ บิล คลินตัน ประธานาธิบดีสหรัฐฯ จากพรรคเดโมแครตในขณะนั้นต้องเผชิญกับกระบวนการถอดถอนจากตำแหน่ง

หรือสูญเสียสถานภาพเดิมไปกันหลายคน กับข้อกล่าวหาประพฤติไม่เหมาะสมทางเพศ ตั้งแต่การใช้สถานะที่เหนือกว่าฉวยโอกาสลวนลามไปจนถึงการข่มขืนลูกจ้างหรือผู้อยู่ใต้บังคับบัญชา . ตอนนั้นเขาอยู่ในจุดสูงสุดของชีวิตการงาน ส่วนฉันเพิ่งจะได้ทำงานแรกหลังจบมหาวิทยาลัย `` . อย่างไรก็ดี ตอนนั้นการแสวงประโยชน์ทางเพศของผู้มีอำนาจไม่ได้ถูกเพ่งเล็งมากเหมือนตอนนี้ ( column2: i was not a gymnast or dancer.

column3: which is in itself limiting. so many amazing teachers from so many disciplines

column1: shreya arora is using her art to explore consent in india 🇮🇳 she has created a paper dress made from printed tweets from india's #metoo movement. shreya says
column2: “i hope every single sexual harasser watches this movement keenly
column3: and is aware of the global community it has created.” 🌎 she thinks that before we can learn what consent is
column4: “we need to unlearn the things we assume are consent. victim blaming often teaches us to assume that if a woman was out alone at night
column6: or had a lot to drink
column7: she was somehow asking for it. to talk about how it is never the victim's fault

column4: we gathered at the crucified woman at emmanuel college.

column1: we didn’t have cell phones. the internet was an academic tool that forward thinking profs were showing their students in libraries. so rumours were passed with whispered urgency
column3: paying tribute to our sisters in montreal.

column1: the crucified woman is meant to represent all women’s suffering. that night
column2: she became for me the unintentional symbol of december 6. while in this age of #metoo we have taken strides and are finding our voices

column3: 13 female students and a female administrator at l'école polytechnique de montréal were murdered because they were women. the shocking impact of their deaths led to december 6 being designated as a national day of remembrance. nearly 30 years later
column4: the effects of this tragedy continue to be felt and women remain targets because of their gender.

column1: the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women is about remembering victims; it is also a time to take action. we each have the opportunity and the responsibility to stand up against misogyny
column3: and hate — and it starts with creating a culture of respect.

column1: it is also an opportunity to consider the women and girls for whom violence is a daily reality
column2: and to remember those who have died as a result of gender-based violence. finally
column3: it is a day for communities to consider concrete actions to eliminate all forms of violence against women and girls.

column1: in addition to the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women on december 6
column2: the international day for the elimination of violence against women takes place on november 25 and marks the first day of the 16 days of activism against gender-based violence

column1: 146846;instagram;2018-12-06 15:08:54;FALSE;"i am grateful that some canadian radio stations thought twice about playing baby it's cold outside because it is sparked an interesting conversation in canada.
i don't really care if you are ""for"" or ""against"" the song - i care that you are talking about it.
i spoke to someone yesterday who
column2: because of the #metoo movement and prior to any ""controversy"" about the song
column3: took a closer and more critical listen to the song and determined it was problematic.

column1: critical thinking is crucial to culture
critical thinking isn't opinion but it can be informed by experiences - particularly the experiences of those who have been affected by whatever is being debated or analyzed.

today is december 6th which is an important date of remembrance for canadians because 14 women died because they were women- women who were trying to pursue their education in a male dominated field and who were called ""feminists"" before they were shot and killed in cold blood.

i don't care if you think ""political correctness"" has gone awry or that #metoo has ""gone too far."" i care that you are talking about issues that are real. issues that you might not feel affected by like rape and consent and violence against women.
these issue are important and not just to women who think the guy in baby it's cold outside is a creep.
they think he's a creep because they know that guy. they've known lots of guys like him. and if men haven't critically examined your practices
column2: they could be that guy supported and defended in a culture that elides the truth about
column4: various forms of violence against women

column1: let's search ourselves and try to work together on proactive solutions.
if you can get that worked up over a song
column2: then i encourage you to get equally as riled for the memory of 14 dead women that stand as stain on women's rights in canada and on canadian history more generally.

column3: за что мне очень и не очень понравился сериал

column1: 🕸️""сабрина - маленькая ведьма"" уже не та. и сравнивать даже не стоит. чего стоит только то удивление
column2: что пушистая жопка салем теперь только реалистично мяукает.
что обожаю женских сильных персонажек? ловите ещё тонну радости - тут они есть.
в которых женщины приносят себя в жертву. сабрина бросает вызов самому сатане
column4: что ей делать. она сетует на необходимость быть девственницей

column2: что все волшебство в сериале и подчинение сатане не что иное
column3: как отсылка к тому самому патриархату. где женщины ""сами желают""
column4: чтобы их съели и ""добровольно"" отдают свою душу владыке.

column3: сексизм в школе. сабрина создает клуб для поддержки девочек
column4: рисует стенгазеты и пытается свергнуть белый патриархат. хотя сама потом окажется в похожем положении.

column5: называя все истории ""охотой на ведьм"". директор школы сабрины прямое олицетворение этого.

column2: когда во время суда сабрину обвинили в том
column3: что она пришла на крещение в свадебном платье ""буквально дав согласие своим видом

column1: 🕸️герой харви как типичная девушка главного героя: беспомощная
column5: и которая ничего не решает. отличный щелчок по носу.

column1: кортни лав (courtney love) выпустила ограниченную коллекцию одежды. она сделала это в сотрудничестве с компанией midnight studios.
рок-звезда является вдовой солиста группы «нирвана» (nirvana) курта кобейна (kurt cobain). он трагически погиб в 1994 году. у 54-летней лав есть 26-летняя дочь фрэнсис бин.
продаваться одежда певицы будет на сайте hypebeast. в коллекции будет представлено несколько интересных образов
column2: созданных на базе многослойных нарядов. в ней имеются футболки с черно-белом изображением самой кортни

– она одна из самых неверно понимаемых женщин
column3: странная личность. но наследие группы hole для меня очень важно. когда оглядываюсь назад
column5: что она оказала большое влияние на музыку. и заслуживает уважения. это влияние было очень реальным и сильным. а что касается движения #metoo
column6: кортни постоянно говорила о подобных вещах и раньше.

column2: a web documentary by tiffany hsiung about the “comfort women”. everything and all about every single violence seems to flashback to me. rape as a weapon of war. rape as a mechanism of control. rape as a culture. i study this. i read and write about this. i experienced sexual harrashment and violence throughout my life. i experienced rape. and every single time it breaks my heart and crush my bone. they are not numbers. herstory is never about numbers
column3: every single story matters. with my life
column4: i felt them running through my bones. the generational traumas. the unresolved wound in our dna memories.

column1: i tried to hold myself while i hold a space bar
column2: tried to hold spaces for these grandmothers and found myself failing in my dark corner of our world.

column1: what did our grandmothers are trying to tell us? this wounded damaged collective womb that keeps on bleeding. we never recover them with the way we let our culture of violence happening over and over. how do you win a war when you hurt your own mother? what do we gain in hurting each other? losses and losses
column2: war after war. my ten year old ask me whether the ww iii is going to happen at his time. i don’t have the answer everytime i see the face of our humanity.

column1: 146910;instagram;2018-12-06 16:34:49;FALSE;"the email i sent out to my students today was focused around permission and practice. i’ve been thinking about this for some time
column2: after a student of mine seemed to freeze a little in class when i placed my hand on her back. it was a gentle gesture to bring her attention towards her spine and yet i felt like i’d really invaded her personal space. i’ve already moved away from hands on adjustments
column3: this was never really an area that felt comfortable for me. i want to provide a safe and caring practice space and offer the idea that yoga is svadhaya - personal enquiry. •

column1: to have trust in your teacher is paramount
column2: but to be able to trust in yourself first is more important. to know what feels right for you without someone who may be place in a 'higher' position moving you there physically
column3: this for me is the best way to practice.

column1: i am only here to offer the possibilities of what this great practice can reveal. thanks to the clear guidance and mentorship of the many wonderful teachers i have worked with along the way
column2: but especially to the tender-open student/teacher relationship i have with my own teacher zoë. the boundaries are clear
column3: we are equal. and this is what we are to one another too in a yoga class situation. •

column1: sometimes i may place my hand on your back
column2: shoulders or hands just to give you an indicator or where you may like to find some space

column1: it would be good to know your thoughts too...thanks for reading. •

column1: از باور کردن دروغ‌هایی که درباره‌تان گفته می‌شود دست بردارید تا تبدیل به همان کسی شوید که واقعا هستید.
اگه این کتاب رو خوندین نظرتون رو با ما در میون بگذارید

دخترها از سراسر دنیا از من می‌پرسن که چطور... چطور وقتی زمین می‌خورم دوباره بلند ‌شم؟ چطور توی زندگی‌م تغییر ایجاد ‌کنم؟ چطور با این ضربۀ روحی کنار بیام؟ چطور دوباره شروع کنم؟ چطور این بچه ها رو بزرگ کنم؟ سؤال‌هایی از این دست که از نظر من همه یک جواب دارند.

بعضی از شماها حتماً از این یادداشت‌ها از من گرفتید... می‌گفتم که «تو یک مبارزی. خیلی قوی هستی. تو هر کاری که بخوای می‌تونی انجام بدی.» اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم. اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی.
و جواب اینه: تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری. دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد. تو جواب رو می‌دونی. تو ابزارش رو داری.

فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» #دختر #دخترها #زنان #فمینیسم #قوی_بودن #اعتماد_به_نفس #مبارزه #خودت_باش #کتاب_کوله_پشتی #کوله_پشتی #برابری #تلاش #کتابفروشی_ملک_یزد #یزد";;en;#خودت_باش_دختر

دخترها از سراسر دنیا از من می‌پرسن که چطور... چطور وقتی زمین می‌خورم دوباره بلند ‌شم؟ چطور توی زندگی‌م تغییر ایجاد ‌کنم؟ چطور با این ضربۀ روحی کنار بیام؟ چطور دوباره شروع کنم؟ چطور این بچه ها رو بزرگ کنم؟ سؤال‌هایی از این دست که از نظر من همه یک جواب دارند.

بعضی از شماها حتماً از این یادداشت‌ها از من گرفتید... می‌گفتم که «تو یک مبارزی. خیلی قوی هستی. تو هر کاری که بخوای می‌تونی انجام بدی.» اما بعد از مدتی متوجه شدم اون جوابی که می‌خواستم رو نمی‌گفتم. اون‌وقت بود که سعی کردم کتابی بنویسم که جواب تمام سؤال‌های شما توش باشه، اگه دوست من بودید یا اگر خودم بودید؛ توی سن بیست، بیست‌وپنج، یا سی سالگی.
و جواب اینه: تو قدرت تغییر زندگی‌ت رو داری. دیگه دنبال پاسخ سؤالاتت توی اینترنت نگرد. تو جواب رو می‌دونی. تو ابزارش رو داری.

فکر کردم اگه این کتاب رو بنویسم و همۀ کشمکش‌های زندگی خودم رو توش بیارم، یا زمان‌هایی که نمی‌دونستم چه‌کار کنم و گیج بودم، وقت‌هایی که زمین خوردم، اشتباه ‌کردم؛ و اگه مسیری که خودم رفتم رو نشونتون بدم، اون‌وقت جرئتی بهتون می‌دم که توی مسیر خودتون هدفمند قدم بردارید. من نخواستم نظاره‌گر غرق شدن شما باشم. من توی محبت کردن آدم خشکی هستم، پس هرکس که مشکلش رو پیش من مطرح کنه باید پیه همه‌چیز رو به تنش مالیده باشه. می‌دونید، «من هم همین‌طور (#metoo)» از قدرتمندترین کلمات زبان انگلیسی هستند. و من از این تفکر یک بستر ساختم. و همچنین از این باور که «من اول شروع می‌کنم.» #دختر #دخترها #زنان #فمینیسم #قوی_بودن #اعتماد_به_نفس #مبارزه #خودت_باش #کتاب_کوله_پشتی #کوله_پشتی #برابری #تلاش #کتابفروشی_ملک_یزد #یزد";"✔ ودت_باش_دختر

column1: 146958;instagram;2018-12-06 17:17:13;FALSE;"i am very proud to be a part of this anthology. as a horror fiction writer
column2: i’m well aware of the fact that mankind is the cruelest animal; that we’re the real monsters. it also makes me keenly aware of the horrible things that occur in our world
column3: and that sexual violence is still one of them. the particular topic of sexual assault and harassment has gotten a lot of attention in the media lately. we all know that this has been happening and mostly all have a friend
column6: who has had an experience with this disgusting epidemic. & we (mostly) never talk about it
column7: because we’ve been conditioned by society to feel ashamed or have been made to feel as if whatever occurred was our fault. because of this
column8: silence became a companion to many
column9: as it seemed the only true safe and sacred space left. the quiet mind
column10: acting as both enemy and friend
column11: was the only warm refuge to hold the secret truths back
column13: wouldn’t it? //we will not be silenced// is an anthology of ground breaking proportions. it does not ask the participant-writers to reveal any secrets
column14: it’s just a buncha grrl power in their #ownvoices and a book of support and tribute to show you and anyone that
column15: although you might feel alone in that silent space

column1: sorry for the inactivity but gosh life has been crazy!
story time!!! so as lots of you know i am a survivor of sexual assault. i went through a trial and testified
column3: and started to heal. but about a month ago i had to go back to court because he had appealed an objection the commonwealth had made and he won the appeal
column4: because the judge ruled that i wouldn’t have to answer the question
column5: but it was the wrong objection to make—she made a mistake. so he was granted another trial
column6: and i have to make the choice of if i want to testify again or just not be involved. in the case that i didn’t testify he would be able to go free
column7: only severing 3 of the 15 years he was convicted for. it’s a bit stressful lol. but if anything is has made me stronger
column8: and i am hardheaded. he cannot get away with what he did to me
column9: and no matter what happens again
column10: i will not go down without a fight.

column1: so that’s why i haven’t been very active! anyways
column3: but it doesn’t mean you’re still not making progress.

column1: 146982;instagram;2018-12-06 17:55:10;FALSE;"we need to be aware that we are constantly teaching our children the rules of consent; and every time we tell them that they have to do something
column2: we are teaching them that their opinions and their bodies don't matter. i totally understand that there's this strange expectation with relatives and that we all feel pressure (as parents and caretakers) to perform specific rituals
column3: but the bodies of our children are not our bodies.

column4: and this needs to be replicated for your kids. kids aren't second-class citizens
column5: they are just smaller humans trying to figure out their world. making them hug or kiss a relative doesn't teach them that there are certain things we have to do in order to fit it
column6: it tells them that they don't matter. this probably sounds totally far-fetched or exaggerated

column1: think about it. how do you feel when you *have* to do something you don't want to do? you build up feelings of shame
column2: guilt or even resentment; it doesn't feel good. we want to be in control of our actions and what happens to our bodies - granted
column3: that's not possible 100% of the time
column4: but in the context of greeting other people? it's totally possible.

column1: before going to a family gathering
column2: i suggest having a conversation with your child(ren). talk about the rituals and let them know that it's okay for them to not participate. i generally empower my kids to use words
column3: such as ""hello!"" or ""it's good to see you!"" instead of physical gestures.  if your friends or relatives have a hard time understanding why your child(ren) don't want to engage
column4: you don't have to feel responsible for your child's actions. remember
column5: they are a separate entity from you - not an extension of your body. let them own their feelings and experiences. if your family members or friends need an explanation
column6: simply say ""my child doesn't want a hug or kiss right now."" you are stating a fact and allowing your child to navigate their own feelings and experiences.

column1: 146985;instagram;2018-12-06 17:56:42;TRUE;;"❄️ snowflake run ❄️ with benny 🐶 this morning. i don’t have a watch pic because i shut it off and forgot to flip it back on when this husky dog ran up on us in the middle of nowhere. wtf. i had a client tell me once that if this happens you need to look the dog in the eye and alpha up on the dog. it was crazy how fast i reacted to this. dog ran up in an unfriendly way ☝️stopped watch ✌️flipped open pepper spray 🖕🏻🖕🏻🖕🏻went all avatar like on this dog (if i only had graces lab playing at that time it would have been epic!!! 🤣@paradise_runs ) it worked!! dog backed down. my instincts took over. i wasn’t flustered ⚡️took action ⚡️i have thought about “what if’s” quite a bit while running. every time i talk to my mom about running she has a new horror story about runners getting picked up - killed- raped - etc. 😣 i tell her she needs to quit watching the news.. she tells me that i need to start. i have thought a lot about how i would react if i thought someone or something would try to harm me. every person & vehicle that i cross paths with i view as a potential threat.. i know this may be a bit excessive.  it’s unfortunate that i/we have to think this way. but i would rather be a bit extra then vulnerable- i carry 3 forms of defense with me at all times while running outside. it’s what helps me feel like i’m doing my part to keep myself safe. today it was good to see me respond so quickly in a situation ⭐️ just something to think about ig ⭐️ so yes distance wasn’t tracked by my watch today but luckily my other tracker @milestone_pod - was able to. be safe out there 💓  #oymambassador #hairstylist  #inkedgirl #explantista #marathoner #procompressionambassador #runnersrepost  #poweryourpassion  #noexcuses #runspiration #strength #runnerscommunity #motherrunner #getafterit #girlswholift
